choices.text:
leaving my parents. I'm 24 now, and I left my home city when i was 15, and went to university. When you are leaving your family with no possibility to see them for atleast years it is very stressful and painful with thoughts.  
So when i had my first child i thought i would handle it. But it is completely the opposite. Being separated from them will be even more emotional painful.  
Done my ultrasound today, i'm entering 18 weeks, so i'll have a less evening sickness and be able to enjoy more the pregnancy.  
Thanks Reddit, i'm happy that i have found you and this wonderful subreddit :)
